  "prompt": "Which IT direct vendor companies sponsors H1B for students who went to school in USA and have experience?",
  "response": "Several IT companies in the United States are known to sponsor H-1B visas for international students who have graduated from U.S. institutions and have relevant experience. While the specific sponsorship policies can vary from year to year and depend on various factors, here are some well-known companies that have a history of sponsoring H-1B visas in the IT sector:\n\n1. **Amazon**\n2. **Google**\n3. **Microsoft**\n4. **IBM**\n5. **Facebook (Meta)**\n6. **Apple**\n7. **Intel**\n8. **Cisco**\n9. **Oracle**\n10. **Salesforce**\n11. **Accenture**\n12. **Capgemini**\n13. **Cognizant**\n14. **Deloitte**\n15. **Tata Consultancy Services (TCS)**\n\nIt\u2019s important to keep in mind that while these companies have sponsored H-1B visas in the past, the decision to sponsor can depend on the applicant's qualifications, the role in question, and the company\u2019s needs at the time. \n\nIf you are a recent graduate looking for H-1B sponsorship, consider:\n\n- Networking with professionals in your field.\n- Attending career fairs and job fairs focused on international students.\n- Utilizing LinkedIn and other job search platforms to find opportunities.\n- Researching which companies are actively hiring in your area of expertise.\n\nMake sure to check each company's career page for the most up-to-date information on their sponsorship policies.",
